transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:47754:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:62496:def: \"The process of restoring DNA after damage. Genomes are subject to damage by chemical and physical agents in the environment (e.g. UV and ionizing radiations, chemical mutagens, fungal and bacterial toxins, etc.) and by free radicals or alkylating agents endogenously generated in metabolism. DNA is also damaged because of errors during its replication. A variety of different DNA repair pathways have been reported that include direct reversal, base excision repair, nucleotide excision repair, photoreactivation, bypass, double-strand break repair pathway, and mismatch repair pathway.\" [PMID:11563486]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:62725:name: obsolete DNA alkylation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:62727:def: \"OBSOLETE. The addition of alkyl groups to many positions on all four bases of DNA. Alkylating agents can also modify the bases of incoming nucleotides in the course of DNA synthesis.\" [ISBN:0716735970]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:62745:name: DNA alkylation repair\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:62747:def: \"The repair of alkylation damage in DNA, e.g. the removal of a non-physiological alkyl group from a nucleobase. This is usually mediated by DNA alkyltransferases.\" [PMID:10946226, PMID:35543797]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:62748:synonym: \"DNA dealkylation involved in DNA repair\" RELATED []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:64327:is_a: GO:0008213 ! protein alkylation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:64356:is_a: GO:0008214 ! protein dealkylation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:65748:name: obsolete indolalkylamine metabolic process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:65750:def: \"OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving indolalkylamines, indole or indole derivatives containing a primary, secondary, or tertiary amine group.\" [GOC:curators]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:65752:synonym: \"indolalkylamine metabolism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:66491:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways involving glycerophospholipids, any derivative of glycerophosphate that contains at least one O-acyl, O-alkyl, or O-alkenyl group attached to the glycerol residue.\" [ISBN:0198506732]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:66503:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of diacylglycerol, a glyceride in which any two of the R groups (positions not specified) are acyl groups while the remaining R group can be either H or an alkyl group.\" [GOC:curators]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:66635:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of platelet activating factor, 1-O-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphocholine, where alkyl = hexadecyl or octadecyl. Platelet activating factor is an inflammatory mediator released from a variety of cells in response to various stimuli.\" [ISBN:0198547684]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:78042:name: phenylalkylamine binding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:78044:def: \"Binding to phenylalkylamine or one of its derivatives.\" [GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:78046:intersection_of: has_primary_input CHEBI:60977 ! phenylalkylamine\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:78748:name: protein alkylation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:78750:def: \"The addition of an alkyl group to a protein amino acid. Alkyl groups are derived from alkanes by removal of one hydrogen atom.\" [GOC:ma]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:78752:synonym: \"protein amino acid alkylation\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:78757:name: protein dealkylation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:78759:def: \"The removal of an alkyl group from a protein amino acid. Alkyl groups are derived from alkanes by removal of one hydrogen atom.\" [GOC:ai]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:78761:synonym: \"protein amino acid dealkylation\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:79103:name: 1-alkyl-2-acetylglycerophosphocholine esterase complex\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:79106:comment: See also the molecular function term '1-alkyl-2-acetylglycerophosphocholine esterase activity ; GO:0003847'.\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:79107:synonym: \"2-acetyl-1-alkylglycerophosphocholine esterase complex\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:79110:intersection_of: capable_of GO:0003847 ! 1-alkyl-2-acetylglycerophosphocholine esterase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:83196:name: alkylglycerone-phosphate synthase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:83198:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 1-acyl-glycerone 3-phosphate + a long-chain alcohol = 1-alkyl-glycerone 3-phosphate + a long-chain acid anion.\" [EC:2.5.1.26]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:83200:synonym: \"alkyl DHAP synthetase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.5.1.26]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:83201:synonym: \"alkyl-DHAP\" RELATED [EC:2.5.1.26]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:83202:synonym: \"alkyl-DHAP synthase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.5.1.26]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:83203:synonym: \"alkyldihydroxyacetone phosphate synthetase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.5.1.26]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:83204:synonym: \"alkyldihydroxyacetonephosphate synthase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.5.1.26]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:83211:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:83965:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:85158:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:85579:name: alkyl hydroperoxide reductase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:86114:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:88692:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:88967:def: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the cleavage of N-terminal leader sequences from membrane prolipoproteins. Hydrolyzes the terminal bond of Xaa-Xbb-Xbb-Cys, in which Xaa is hydrophobic (preferably Leu), Xbb is often Ser or Ala, Xcc is often Gly or Ala, and the Cys is alkylated on sulfur with a diacylglyceryl group.\" [EC:3.4.23.36]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:92759:name: alkyl hydroperoxide reductase complex\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:92762:comment: See also the molecular function term 'alkyl hydroperoxide reductase activity ; GO:0008785'.\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:97758:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:100908:def: \"The chemical reactions using mycothiol to convert an alkylating agent to an S-conjugate of mycothiol. The latter is cleaved to release mercapturic acid which is excreted from the cell.\" [GOC:pz]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:100909:synonym: \"mycothiol-dependent detoxification of alkylating agent\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:101420:name: methylthioalkylmalate synthase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:101422:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + an omega-(methylsulfanyl)-2-oxoalkanoate + H2O = a 2-(omega-methylsulfanyl)alkylmalate + CoA + H+.\" [RHEA:50624]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:101430:is_a: GO:0046912 ! acyltransferase activity, acyl groups converted into alkyl on transfer\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:104430:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:105069:def: \"Any process that modulates the chemical reactions and pathways involving any of a class of organic compounds that contain the carbonyl group, CO, and in which the carbonyl group is bonded only to carbon atoms. The general formula for a ketone is RCOR, where R and R are alkyl or aryl groups.\" [GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:115647:synonym: \"alkylphosphonate ABC transporter activity\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:115648:synonym: \"alkylphosphonate transmembrane transporter activity\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:115649:synonym: \"alkylphosphonate transmembrane-transporting ATPase activity\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:115651:synonym: \"ATPase-coupled alkylphosphonate transmembrane transporter activity\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:115738:def: \"Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: vitamin B12(out) + ATP + H2O = ADP + an vitamin B12(in) + H+ + phosphate. Vitamin B12 is alkylcob(III)alamin.\" [GOC:pz, RHEA:17873]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:118565:synonym: \"alkylphosphonate transport\" NARROW []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:125156:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:128412:name: transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:128415:def: \"Catalysis of the transfer of an alkyl or aryl (but not methyl) group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).\" [EC:2.5.1.-]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:128418:synonym: \"transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:128444:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:128747:name: trialkylsulfonium hydrolase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:128751:synonym: \"trialkylsulphonium hydrolase activity\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:139601:name: obsolete atrazine N-dealkylase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:140222:name: linear primary-alkylsulfatase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:140224:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a primary linear alkyl sulfate ester + H2O = a primary alcohol + H+ + sulfate.\" [RHEA:67908]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:140225:synonym: \"alkyl sulfatase activity\" BROAD []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:140636:def: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: alkyl halide + H2O = alcohol + HCl. Substrates are 1,3(R),4,6(R)-tetrachloro-1,4-cyclohexadiene (forms 2,4,5-trichloro-2,5-cyclohexadiene-1-ol) and 2,4,5-trichloro-2,5-cyclohexadiene-1-ol (forms 2,5-dichloro-2,5-cyclohexadiene-1,4-diol).\" [PMID:10464214]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:141381:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: alkylphosphonic acid = R-CH3 + phosphate. Substrates include aminomethylphosphonic acid (AMPA) (forms methylamine), dimethylphosphinic acid (forms methylphosphonic acid), glyphosate (forms sarcosine) and methylphosphonic acid (forms phosphate).\" [PMID:3804975]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:141388:name: alkylmercury lyase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:141390:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: an alkylmercury + H+ = an alkane + Hg2+.\" [RHEA:18777]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:141391:synonym: \"alkylmercury mercuric-lyase (alkane-forming)\" RELATED [EC:4.99.1.2]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:141392:synonym: \"alkylmercury mercuric-lyase activity\" RELATED [EC:4.99.1.2]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:142169:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways involving dimethyl sulfoxide, DMSO (C2H6OS), an alkyl sulfoxide that is practically odorless in its purified form. As a highly polar organic liquid, it is a powerful solvent. Its biological activities include the ability to penetrate plant and animal tissues and to preserve living cells during freezing.\" [GOC:curators]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:142646:def: \"OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving p-cymene, 1-methyl-4-isopropylbenzene, one of the alkyl-substituted aromatic hydrocarbons found in volatile oils from over 100 plants.\" [UM-BBD_pathwayID:pcy]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:142776:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways involving propylene, an alkene produced by catalytic or thermal cracking of hydrocarbons or as a by-product of petroleum refining. It is used mainly in the preparation of alkylates for gasoline and in the production of polypropylene, acrylonitrile, propylene oxide and a number of other industrial chemicals.\" [GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:144555:is_a: GO:0046912 ! acyltransferase activity, acyl groups converted into alkyl on transfer\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:146737:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of p-cymene, 1-methyl-4-isopropylbenzene, one of the alkyl-substituted aromatic hydrocarbons found in volatile oils from over 100 plants.\" [GOC:ai]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:150294:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphonates, any organic compounds containing one or more C-PO(OH)2 or C-PO(OR)2 (with R=alkyl, aryl) groups. Metabolism of phosphonic acid itself, an inorganic compound without the biochemically relevant C-P bond, is not included.\" [GOC:js, ISBN:0721662544]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:151094:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of phosphonates, any organic compound containing one or more C-PO(OH)2 or C-PO(OR)2 (with R=alkyl, aryl) groups. Catabolism of phosphonic acid itself, an inorganic compound without the biochemically relevant C-P bond, is not included.\" [GOC:js]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:162065:name: aralkylamine dehydrogenase (azurin) activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:162067:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: an aralkylamine + H2O + 2 oxidized [azurin] = an aromatic aldehyde + 2 H+ + NH4+ + 2 reduced [azurin].\" [PMID:10506161, RHEA:47796]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:162068:synonym: \"aralkylamine:(azurin) oxidoreductase (deaminating) activity\" EXACT [EC:1.4.9.2]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:165782:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:183674:name: alkylated DNA binding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:183676:def: \"Binding to an alkylated residue in DNA.\" [GOC:mah]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:183683:name: O6-alkylguanine-DNA binding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:183685:def: \"Binding to an O6-alkylguanine adduct in DNA.\" [GOC:mah, PMID:16679453]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:183686:is_a: GO:0032131 ! alkylated DNA binding\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:192491:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of phosphonates, any organic compound containing one or more C-PO(OH)2 or C-PO(OR)2 (with R=alkyl, aryl) groups. Synthesis of phosphonic acid itself, an inorganic compound without the biochemically relevant C-P bond, is not included.\" [GOC:js]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:195320:name: response to alkyl hydroperoxide\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:195322:def: \"Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an alkyl hydroperoxide stimulus. Alkyl hydroperoxides are monosubstitution products of hydrogen peroxide, HOOH, where the substituent is an alkyl group.\" [GOC:mah]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:195324:intersection_of: has_primary_input CHEBI:61050 ! alkyl hydroperoxide\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:202855:synonym: \"D-galactose-6-sulfate:alkyltransferase (cyclizing) activity\" RELATED [EC:2.5.1.5]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:202861:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:202881:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:202894:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:202911:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:202925:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:202939:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:202953:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:203219:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenylyl sulfate + a thiol = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + an S-alkyl thiosulfate.\" [EC:2.8.2.16]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:205626:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:210857:name: obsolete N-cyclopropylammelide alkylamino hydrolase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220303:name: DNA dealkylation\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220305:def: \"The removal of an alkyl group from one or more nucleotides within an DNA molecule.\" [GOC:bf]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:220375:comment: This reaction directly reverses the alkylation on a nucleotide within DNA. Do not confuse with 5-methylcytosine dioxygenase activity ; GO:0070579, which removes the methyl group from position 5 of cytosine in DNA via oxidation of the 5-methylcytosine, followed by removal of the oxidated base by the base excision repair system.\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:221303:is_a: GO:0050497 ! alkylthioltransferase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:231655:is_a: GO:0046912 ! acyltransferase activity, acyl groups converted into alkyl on transfer\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:240424:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways involving any of a class of organic compounds that contain the carbonyl group, CO, and in which the carbonyl group is bonded only to carbon atoms, as carried out by individual cells. The general formula for a ketone is RCOR, where R and R are alkyl or aryl groups.\" [GOC:jl, ISBN:0787650153]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:240435:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of ketones, a class of organic compounds that contain the carbonyl group, CO, and in which the carbonyl group is bonded only to carbon atoms. The general formula for a ketone is RCOR, where R and R are alkyl or aryl groups.\" [GOC:curators]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:240448:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of ketones, a class of organic compounds that contain the carbonyl group, CO, and in which the carbonyl group is bonded only to carbon atoms. The general formula for a ketone is RCOR, where R and R are alkyl or aryl groups.\" [GOC:curators]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:240813:def: \"OBSOLETE. The aerobic chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of dimethylsilanediol, the smallest member of the dialkylsilanediols. Dimethylsilanediol is the monomer of polydimethylsiloxane, a compound which can be found in a wide range of industrial and consumer products.\" [GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:250309:def: \"Binding to an alcohol, any of a class of alkyl compounds containing a hydroxyl group.\" [GOC:jl, ISBN:0198506732]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:256131:is_a: GO:0003905 ! alkylbase DNA N-glycosylase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:256149:def: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of alkylated DNA; recognizes and removes both N-3- and N-7-methyl purines by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the target damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar. The reaction releases a free base and leaves an apurinic (AP) site.\" [PMID:10375529]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:256511:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:258403:is_a: GO:0003905 ! alkylbase DNA N-glycosylase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:258427:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:258437:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:266817:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281786:name: obsolete indolalkylamine catabolic process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281788:def: \"OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of indolalkylamines, indole or indole derivatives containing a primary, secondary, or tertiary amine group.\" [GOC:curators]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281790:synonym: \"indolalkylamine breakdown\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281791:synonym: \"indolalkylamine catabolism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281792:synonym: \"indolalkylamine degradation\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281797:name: indolalkylamine biosynthetic process\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281799:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of indolalkylamines, indole or indole derivatives containing a primary, secondary, or tertiary amine group.\" [GOC:curators]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281800:synonym: \"indolalkylamine anabolism\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281801:synonym: \"indolalkylamine biosynthesis\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281802:synonym: \"indolalkylamine formation\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281803:synonym: \"indolalkylamine synthesis\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:281806:intersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:38631 ! aminoalkylindole\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:283298:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways involving diacylglycerol, a glyceride in which any two of the R groups (positions not specified) are acyl groups while the remaining R group can be either H or an alkyl group.\" [PMID:11481335]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:283308:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of diacylglycerol, a glyceride in which any two of the R groups (positions not specified) are acyl groups while the remaining R group can be either H or an alkyl group.\" [PMID:11717312]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:284614:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways involving dimethylsilanediol, the smallest member of the dialkylsilanediols. Dimethylsilanediol is the monomer of polydimethylsiloxane, a compound which can be found in a wide range of industrial and consumer products.\" [GOC:ai]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:284801:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways involving platelet activating factor, 1-O-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphocholine, where alkyl = hexadecyl or octadecyl. Platelet activating factor is an inflammatory mediator released from a variety of cells in response to various stimuli.\" [ISBN:0198547684]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:284839:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of glycerophospholipids, any derivative of glycerophosphate that contains at least one O-acyl, O-alkyl, or O-alkenyl group attached to the glycerol residue.\" [ISBN:0198506732]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:284853:def: \"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glycerophospholipids, any derivative of glycerophosphate that contains at least one O-acyl, O-alkyl, or O-alkenyl group attached to the glycerol residue.\" [ISBN:0198506732]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:289597:name: acyltransferase activity, acyl groups converted into alkyl on transfer\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:289599:def: \"Catalysis of the transfer of an acyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor), with the acyl group being converted into alkyl on transfer.\" [EC:2.3.3.-, GOC:jl]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:289600:synonym: \"acyltransferase, acyl groups converted into alkyl on transfer\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:289601:synonym: \"transferase activity, transferring acyl groups, acyl groups converted into alkyl on transfer\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:291706:synonym: \"3-alkylcatechol 2,3-dioxygenase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.13.11.25]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293079:name: alkylglycerophosphate 2-O-acetyltransferase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293081:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 1-alkyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + acetyl-CoA = 1-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + CoA.\" [EC:2.3.1.105, RHEA:18557]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293082:synonym: \"acetyl-CoA:1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate 2-O-acetyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.3.1.105]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293083:synonym: \"alkyllyso-GP:acetyl-CoA acetyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.3.1.105]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293195:name: 1-alkyl-2-acetylglycerol O-acyltransferase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293197:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 1-O-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycerol + acyl-CoA = 1-O-alkyl-2-acetyl-3-acyl-sn-glycerol + CoA.\" [EC:2.3.1.125, MetaCyc:2.3.1.125-RXN]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293199:synonym: \"acyl-CoA:1-O-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycerol O-acyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.3.1.125]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293342:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 1-alkyl-2-lyso-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine + 1-alkyl-2-arachidonyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine = 1-alkyl-2-lyso-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + 1-alkyl-2-arachidonyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine.\" [EC:2.3.1.147, MetaCyc:2.3.1.147-RXN]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293367:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 1-radyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospholipid + 1-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine = 1-alkyl-2-lyso-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + 1-radyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycero-3-phospholipid.\" [EC:2.3.1.149, MetaCyc:2.3.1.149-RXN]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293368:synonym: \"1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine:1-organyl-2-lyso-sn-glycero-3-phospholipid acetyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.3.1.149]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293406:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: an alcohol + 1-O-trans-cinnamoyl-beta-D-glucopyranose = beta-D-glucose + alkyl cinnamate.\" [EC:2.3.1.152, MetaCyc:2.3.1.152-RXN]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293586:name: 1-alkylglycerophosphocholine O-acyltransferase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293588:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + acyl-CoA = 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + CoA.\" [EC:2.3.1.63, MetaCyc:2.3.1.63-RXN]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293589:synonym: \"acyl-CoA:1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine O-acyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.3.1.63]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293604:name: 1-alkylglycerophosphocholine O-acetyltransferase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293606:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + acetyl-CoA = 1-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + CoA.\" [EC:2.3.1.67, MetaCyc:2.3.1.67-RXN]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293607:synonym: \"1-alkyl-2-lyso-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine acetyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.3.1.67]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293608:synonym: \"1-alkyl-2-lysolecithin acetyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.3.1.67]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293609:synonym: \"acetyl-CoA:1-alkyl-2-lyso-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine 2-O-acetyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.3.1.67]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293610:synonym: \"acetyl-CoA:1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine 2-O-acetyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.3.1.67]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:293612:synonym: \"acyl-CoA:1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine acyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.3.1.67]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:295204:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:295266:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296413:name: triglucosylalkylacylglycerol sulfotransferase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296415:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: alpha-D-glucosyl-1,6-alpha-D-glucosyl-1,6-alpha-D-glucosyl-1,3-1-O-alkyl-2-O-acylglycerol + 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate = 6-sulfo-alpha-D-glucosyl-1,6-alpha-D-glucosyl-1,6-alpha-D-glucosyl-1,3-1-O-alkyl-2-O-acylglycerol + adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate.\" [EC:2.8.2.19, MetaCyc:2.8.2.19-RXN]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296416:synonym: \"3'-phosphoadenylyl-sulfate:triglucosyl-1-O-alkyl-2-O-acylglycerol 6-sulfotransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.8.2.19]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296417:synonym: \"triglucosylalkylacylglycerol sulphotransferase activity\" EXACT []\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296418:synonym: \"triglucosylmonoalkylmonoacyl sulfotransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.8.2.19]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296679:name: acetylalkylglycerol acetylhydrolase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296681:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2-acetyl-1-alkyl-sn-glycerol + H2O = 1-alkyl-sn-glycerol + acetate + H+.\" [EC:3.1.1.71, RHEA:11552]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296682:synonym: \"2-acetyl-1-alkyl-sn-glycerol acetylhydrolase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.1.1.71]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296683:synonym: \"alkylacetylglycerol acetylhydrolase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.1.1.71]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296879:name: alkylglycerophosphoethanolamine phosphodiesterase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296881:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + 1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine = ethanolamine + 1-alkyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate.\" [EC:3.1.4.39, MetaCyc:3.1.4.39-RXN]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:296882:synonym: \"1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine ethanolaminehydrolase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.1.4.39]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297251:name: arylalkyl acylamidase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297253:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + N-acetylarylalkylamine = acetate + arylalkylamine.\" [EC:3.5.1.76, MetaCyc:3.5.1.76-RXN]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297254:synonym: \"aralkyl acylamidase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.5.1.76]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297255:synonym: \"N-acetylarylalkylamine amidohydrolase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.5.1.76]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297479:name: 2,2-dialkylglycine decarboxylase (pyruvate) activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297481:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2,2-dialkylglycine + H+ + pyruvate = L-alanine + CO2 + dialkyl ketone.\" [EC:4.1.1.64, RHEA:16073]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297482:synonym: \"2,2-dialkyl-2-amino acid-pyruvate aminotransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:4.1.1.64]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297483:synonym: \"2,2-dialkylglycine carboxy-lyase (amino-transferring)\" RELATED [EC:4.1.1.64]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297484:synonym: \"2,2-dialkylglycine carboxy-lyase (amino-transferring; L-alanine-forming)\" RELATED [EC:4.1.1.64]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297485:synonym: \"alpha-dialkyl amino acid transaminase activity\" RELATED [EC:4.1.1.64]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297486:synonym: \"dialkyl amino acid (pyruvate) decarboxylase activity\" RELATED [EC:4.1.1.64]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297487:synonym: \"dialkylamino-acid decarboxylase (pyruvate)\" RELATED [EC:4.1.1.64]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297688:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:297927:is_a: GO:0016765 ! transferase activity, transferring alkyl or aryl (other than methyl) groups\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300451:synonym: \"S-adenosyl-L-methionine alkyltransferase (cyclizing) activity\" RELATED [EC:4.4.1.42]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300808:name: alkylacetylglycerophosphatase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300810:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 1-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + H2O = 2-acetyl-1-alkyl-sn-glycerol + phosphate.\" [RHEA:18221]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300811:synonym: \"1-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate phosphohydrolase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.1.3.59]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300812:synonym: \"1-alkyl-2-lyso-sn-glycero-3-P:acetyl-CoA acetyltransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.1.3.59]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300813:synonym: \"alkylacetylglycerophosphate phosphatase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.1.3.59]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300823:name: alkylamidase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300836:name: alkylglycerol kinase activity\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300838:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 1-alkyl-sn-glycerol + ATP = 1-alkyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + ADP + 2 H+.\" [EC:2.7.1.93, RHEA:16937]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300839:synonym: \"1-alkylglycerol kinase (phosphorylating)\" RELATED [EC:2.7.1.93]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300840:synonym: \"alkylglycerol phosphotransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.7.1.93]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300841:synonym: \"ATP-alkylglycerol phosphotransferase activity\" RELATED [EC:2.7.1.93]\nsrc/ontology/go-edit.obo:300842:synonym: \"ATP:1-alkyl-sn-g